# {{project_title}}

GitHub Copilot research experiments, powered by
[`copilot-experiments`](https://github.com/dbroeglin/github-copilot-lab).

## Layout

```
experiments/        # Python experiment definitions (one or more per file)
fixtures/           # starting workspaces copied for each trial
results/            # collected run artifacts + SQLite index (gitignored)
.apm/               # APM agent context (instructions, skills, prompts)
```

## Usage

```bash
uv sync

uv sync

# validate the whole pipeline without spending credits (mock Copilot; persists nothing)
uv run copilot-experiments run --dry-run

# run for real (requires an authenticated `copilot`, or BYOK env vars)
uv run copilot-experiments run
uv run copilot-experiments show --last

# explore results
uv run copilot-experiments list
uv run copilot-experiments inspect <run-id> --variant <slug> --trial 1
```

> `--dry-run` runs the whole pipeline with a mock Copilot inside a temp dir, checks each stage
> produced its artifact (workspace, log, metrics, analysis, a non-empty diff, verify, summary,
> index), then deletes everything — it persists nothing and uses no credits. The mock does
> **not** solve the task, so it validates plumbing, not effectiveness; run without `--dry-run`
> to capture real data to `show`, `analyze`, or `inspect`.

## Writing experiments

See `experiments/example_fix_bug.py`. An experiment is an `Experiment` object combining a
`Task` (prompt + workspace fixture + optional `verify` command) with a list of `Variant`s
(the parameter matrix: model, reasoning effort, agent, or BYOK provider).

## Agent context (APM)

This repo uses [APM](https://github.com/microsoft/apm) to manage Copilot context.

```bash
apm install              # resolve declared dependencies
apm compile -t copilot   # generate .github/copilot-instructions.md
```
